{"word":"νεικέω","slug":"νεικέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νεικέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νεῖκος'><el>νεῖκος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to quarrel</i> or <i>wrangle with</i> one, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>νεικέων</el>, <i>obstinately</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to rail at, abuse, upbraid, revile</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}